File: The cumulative number of COVID-19 cases in the country now stands at 693,359. Flickr.com/AIDSVaccine JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Health reported 888 new cases of COVID-19 in the country. The cumulative number of COVID-19 cases in the country now stands at 693,359. READ: COVID-19: Health Minister warns SA of second wave The death toll now stands at 17,863 after 83 more people died of COVID-19. Recoveries now stand at 624,659 which translates to a recovery rate of 90 percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs